    • Method Detail

      • runApp

        public void runApp(java.lang.String app,
                   java.lang.String[] argsArray,
                   java.io.InputStream inputStream,
                   java.io.OutputStream outputStream)
            throws AbstractApplicationException,
                   ShellException
        Run the application as specified by the application command keyword and arguments.
        Parameters:
        app - String containing the keyword that specifies what application to run.
        argsArray - String array containing the arguments to pass to the applications for running.
        inputStream - InputStream for the application to get input from, if needed.
        outputStream - OutputStream for the application to write its output to.
        Throws:
        AbstractApplicationException - If an exception happens while running an application.
        ShellException - If an unsupported or invalid application command is detected.
